 work of Cohen et al. (FOCS 19) that gave a randomized\n$\\tilde{O}(N)$-time algorithm for inverting Eulerian Laplacian matrices. A\nrunning theme throughout these contributions is an analysis of \"cycle-lifted\ngraphs\", where we take a graph and \"lift\" it to a new graph whose adjacency\nmatrix is the tensor product of the original adjacency matrix and a directed\ncycle (or variants of one).\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Dec 2019 06:12:50 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 20 Apr 2020 04:08:54 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 11 Mar 2022 07:40:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-14"}
